title: Was a Coral Reef Taller Than the Empire State Building Discovered in the Great Barrier Reef?
subtitle: It was the first detached reef to have been discovered in the area since the late 1800s.
author: Madison Dapcevich
vclaim: Australian scientists discovered a 1,600-foot-tall detached coral reef in the Great Barrier Reef, making it the first to be discovered in the region over a century.
